      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so if we're looking at it from that perspective, wouldn't you say that prioritizing certain groups actually creates a \"reverse\" inequality where the most capable people—regardless of race—get sidelined? like, if an individual is objectively more qualified but loses a spot because of a quota or a diversity goal, isn't that a fundamental failure of the system to recognize true excellence?",
